# Dynamic programming. Repeatedly cumulate offsets of squares of d.
# i.e. build counts of how many times each sum of squares occurs.
Count ← (
  d ← ˙×⇡10
  Trim ← ⬚0↙+1×81
  # Offset copies of accum by each of `d`, then trim
  ⍥(Trim⊃⋅∘⊙∘(/+⬚0≡◇⊂⊙¤≡(□˜↯0)d))⊙1 ⟜∘
  Ids ← ⨬(⍢(/+˙×⊥₁₀|↧⊃≠₁≠₈₉)|0)⊸=₀
  ⊙◌/+▽=89≡Ids°⊏ # Sum counts where end result is 89.
)
≡(&p$"10^_: \t_"⟜Count)↘1⇡17
